 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_sp3">
  <title>September 2017 (Initial Release of &productname; 12 SP3)</title>

  <xi:include href="common_docupdates_sp3_i.xml"/>

  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry os="sles">
     <term><xref linkend="cha.install"/></term>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       In <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.s390.part"/>, adjusted a link to point
       to a more appropriate section in the <citetitle>&storage_guide;</citetitle>
       (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1042060"/>).
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.deployment.prep_boot"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed all documentation about connecting to a VNC server with a
        Java-capable browser. Java is no longer supported by most browsers for
        security reasons.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Modified PXE boot to accommodate UEFI (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1006558"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.deployment.prep_boot.mksusecd"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.add-ons"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Moved <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.package-hub"/> from the chapter
        <xref linkend="cha.install"/> to this chapter.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.sdk" />, added information about the support
        status of the SDK.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="pro.add-ons.extensions" />, mentioned new entry in
        &yast; to directly install extensions and modules (Fate #321044).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.background"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="sec.update.nmm.repositories" />, updated repository model
        with &slea; 12 SP3.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.update.lifecyclereport" /> (Fate #322059).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="sec.update.nmm.sles-mod-repositories"/>, mentioned that a certain
        module is not available on &power; (<link
         xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1048670"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="sec.update.nmm.repositories.origin"/>, rephrased a
        sentence (<link
         xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1048672"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Updated <xref linkend="fig.update.sle.paths-overview" />.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added information about offline and online upgrading methods to <xref linkend="sec.update.sle.methods" />.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added backup of package and repository list to <xref linkend="sec.update.prep.backup.packagelist" />.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Mentioned zypper and &yast; as the suggested methods for Service Pack migration in
        <xref linkend="sec.update.sle.methods" />.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="note.update.prep.backup.package_amount"/> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1045649"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Corrected terminology in the introduction to the chapter (<link
         xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1048680"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="sec.update.sle.paths"/>, added missing version numbers
        (<link
         xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1048675"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Added <xref linkend="sec.update.prep.update"/> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1051670"/>).</para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.offline"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added information about migration options with &susemgr;, see
        <xref linkend="sec.update.sle.manager" /> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1035716"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="sec.update.sle.offline.automated" />, mentioned that DVD
        or ISO are needed.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.online"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        When upgrading with plain zypper, a solution for a kernel version
        conflict needs to be picked, see <xref
        linkend="sec.update.migr.plainzypper.onlinemigr" /> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1032595"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Automatic LUN scanning on &zseries; only works with NPIV enabled, see <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.s390.part.zfcp" />.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        SCC, SMT and SUMA repositories can be used for online migration, see
        <xref linkend="sec.update.migr.workflow" /> (Doc Comment #32436).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        In <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.uefi"/>, fixed a typo in an
        installation entry example (<link
         xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1051387"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_sp2_maint1">
  <title>April 2017 (Maintenance Release of &productname; 12 SP2)</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.zseries"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Mentioned possibility of using <filename>susehmc.ins</filename>
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1009081"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="sec.update.modlifecycle"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added link to Module Life Cycles Web site
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1014266"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
