      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 10. Installing Add-On Products  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.add-ons" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated chapter to reflect the software changes to the former &yast;
        <guimenu>&scc; Configuration</guimenu> dialog (now called
        <guimenu>Product Registration</guimenu>) and the &yast; <guimenu>Add-On
        Products</guimenu> module (Fate #318800).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 14. Advanced Disk Setup -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.advdisk" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Mentioned that subvolumes for <filename>/var/lib/mariadb</filename>,
        <filename>/var/lib/pgsql</filename>, and
        <filename>/var/lib/libvirt/images</filename> are created with the
        option <literal>no copy on write</literal> by default to avoid
        extensive fragmenting with Btrfs.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Subscription Management</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The chapter about registering clients at a &smtool; server has been
        replaced by <xref linkend="smt.client" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
<!-- III Updating and Upgrading SUSE Linux Enterprise -->
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="part.update" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Split former update chapter into several independent chapters and
        combined them under this new part.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed &yast; Wagon chapter, as &yast; Wagon is unsupported for
        &productname; &productnumber;.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added new chapter: <xref linkend="cha.update.online"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.update.prep.mariadb"/> and
        <xref linkend="sec.update.prep.postgresql"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Integrated various new features: Fate #315161, Fate #318636, Fate
        #319128, Fate #319129, Fate #319138, Fate #319140.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Fixed path to <filename>zpxe.exec</filename>
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=937511"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Added the <literal>https</literal> protocol to
        <xref
        linkend="sec.boot_parameters.list.install_source"/>
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=951421"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Consistent use of <command>yast</command>,
        <command>yast2.ssh</command>, <command>yast.ssh</command> for SSH based
        installation
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=956060"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Consistent spelling of boot parameters
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=956054"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        PowerKVM: virt-install does not know about SLES12
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=880918"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        IBM &ppc;: Starting an X-Server after an Upgrade
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=948980"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added documentation on the boot process for IBM &zseries;
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=942772"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Description of encrypted <filename>/</filename> and
        <filename>/boot</filename> on Btrfs was missing. Added an important
        note in <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.inst_mode.partitioning"/> and
        <xref
        linkend="sec.yast.btrfs"/>
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=926951"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Zypper multiversion kernels should be mentioned for SP2 Update
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=753809"></link>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        SLES 12 Deployment Guide errors for zPXE installations
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=944384"/>).
