 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga">
  <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>

<!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->

  <xi:include href="common_docupdates_ga_i.xml"/>

  <variablelist>
<!-- 2. Installation on AMD64 and Intel 64 -->
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.x86"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated system requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 3. Installation on IBM POWER  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.power"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added POWER8 to the list of supported hardware (Fate #315272).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sls; 12 for POWER has moved to Little Endian. Updated affected parts
        of the documentation.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 4. Installation on IBM System z -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.zseries"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the list of supported platforms: Removed IBM Series z9 and z10
        machines and added IBM zEnterprise BC12.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the memory and disk space requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed instructions on how to IPL from tape&mdash;this is no longer
        supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Rewrote large parts of <xref linkend="sec.prep.netcfg"/> to remove
        redundant information and make it more concise.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed references to Token Ring, which is no longer supported (Fate
        #313154).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 6. Installation with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.install"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote the chapter because of the new installation
        workflow.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation routine now supports setting up multiple network
        devices during the installation (Fate #315680):
        <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.network"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation proposal contains a separate
        <filename>/home</filename> partition formatted with XFS (Fate #316637
        and Fate #316624): <xref
        linkend="sec.boot_parameters.inst_mode.partitioning"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed occurrences of the &yast; Repair module which has been dropped
        (Fate #308670).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Update repositories are added after having registered with &scc; and
        can be used during installation (Fate #312012):
        <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Extensions and modules can be added to the system during the
        installation (Fate #316548):
        <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.conf.manual.cc"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sled; can be installed as an add-on on top of &sls; (Fate #316436):
        <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        The HW crypto stack for IBM &zseries; can be selected for installation
        via a pattern (Fate #316143):
        <xref linkend="sec.boot_parameters.proposal.sofware"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Automatically importing SSH keys from a previous installation can be
        disabled (Fate #314982).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 7. Updating SUSE Linux Enterprise -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added new section: <xref linkend="sec.update.sle.methods"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 8. Setting Up Hardware Components with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.yast.hw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed the following sections as the respective &yast; modules are no
        longer included: <citetitle>Hardware Information</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Setting Up Graphics Card and Monitor</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Mouse Model</citetitle>, and <citetitle>Setting Up a
        Scanner</citetitle>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed content about mouse setup and adjusted
        <xref linkend="sec.yast.hw.keym"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 9. Installing or Removing Software -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.yast.sw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> because of changes in
        the &gnome; software updater.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 10. Installing Add-On Products  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.add-ons"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Installing add-on products or software extensions is now also possible
        without access to physical media. Added the following new sections:
        <xref linkend="sec.update.registersystem"/> and
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.extensions"/>. Modified
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.install"/> accordingly.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 16. Subscription Management -->
    <term>Subscription Management</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        For registering clients against an &smt; server,
        <command>suse_register</command> has been replaced with
        <command>SUSEConnect</command> (Fate #316585).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated section <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=839692"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed section <citetitle>Using Fingerprint
        Authentication</citetitle>. Further minor corrections and additions
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857680"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed obsolete parameter <literal>OsaMedium</literal> from parmfile
        and Cobbler examples
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=860404"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added instructions on how to add secondary languages during
        installation
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=870482"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Multiversion feature (more than one kernel installed) is enabled by
        default
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Warn about incompatible Kernel Module Packages (KPMs)
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
